HEADWORD: Factionary
<hw>Fac"tion*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>factionnaire</ets>, L. <ets>factionarius</ets> the head of a
company of charioteers.]</ety> <def>Belonging to a faction; being a
partisan; taking sides.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Always <qex>factionary</qex> on the party of your general.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Factioner</ent>⟦br⟧
